olive oil
1 packet button mushrooms
1 Brown Onion
2 clove garlic
1 packet Mild Chorizo
30 g butter
1 tin tinned cherry tomatoes
1 sachet beef-style stock powder
1 packet orecchiette
1.66 cup boiling water
1 tsp brown sugar
1 bag parsley
1 packet beef & pork mince
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Boil the kettle. Thinly slice button mushrooms. Finely chop onion and garlic. Roughly chop mild chorizo.

• In a large saucepan, heat half the butter and a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook chorizo, until browned, 4-5 minutes.
• Add mushrooms and cook until browned and softened, 5-6 minutes.
• Add beef & pork mince and onion and cook, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 4-5 minutes.
• Add garlic and Aussie spice blend and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.

• Add tinned cherry tomatoes, beef-style stock powder, orecchiette and the boiling water and bring to the boil.
• Reduce heat to medium and cover with a lid. Simmer, stirring occasionally, until orecchiette is cooked through, 14-16 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, stir in the brown sugar and remaining butter. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

TIP: Add a splash more water if the sauce looks too thick.

• Divide one pot beef, pork and chorizo orecchiette between bowls.
• Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese and tear over parsley to serve. Enjoy!
Little cooks: Help tear over the herbs and sprinkle the cheese on top.